PRIVACY POLICY
HaloPlus respects and protects the privacy of individuals from all official platforms, including websites, apps, and user communities related to HaloPlus. This Privacy Policy outlines how we collect, use, and protect your data when using HaloPlus on iOS. Without your prior consent, we will not intentionally disclose any information related to your personal privacy to third parties unless explicitly stated in this document.
1. Information We Collect
a. Personal Information
We do not collect Personal Information. Personal Information includes details such as your geographical location, name, address, email, telephone number, device-stored information, or any identifiable information about you or others.
b. Non-Personal Information
When you interact with our app, we may collect non-personal information, such as:
Device Information
:
Model, OS version, screen resolution, battery usage, storage usage, and network state (Wi-Fi, cellular).
Application data such as version, distribution channel, and runtime details.
Language and time zone settings.
Usage Data
:
Number of clicks, time spent on specific pages, app usage frequency, and feature engagement.
System permissions status, app performance metrics, and error logs.
Monetization and Analytics
:
Third-party SDKs may collect data such as your
Apple IDFA (Identifier for Advertisers)
, demographic data (e.g., country from IP address), and data to combat fraud.
The collected data helps us enhance app performance and provide a personalized experience. We do not sell this data to third parties.
2. Permissions We Request
To ensure the app functions correctly, we may request the following permissions:
Location
:
Approximate location (network-based).
Precise location (GPS and network-based).
Photos
:
Read the contents of your photo library.
Save edited photos or videos directly to your library.
Camera
:
Take photos and videos for app functionalities.
You may opt-out of granting these permissions, but certain features may not work properly as a result.
3. How We Use Collected Information
a. Personal Information
Since we do not collect Personal Information, we do not use or store it.
b. Non-Personal Information
We may use Non-Personal Information for:
Personalized User Experience
: Understanding trends in user behavior to enhance app features.
Service Improvement
: Ensuring smooth functionality, identifying errors, and optimizing performance.
Development Purposes
: Supporting market research and product improvements.
4. Data Sharing and Third-Party Integration
Analytics and Monetization
:
We use third-party services like Firebase, Google AdMob, and Apple SKAdNetwork to analyze app performance and serve advertisements. These third parties may collect data as governed by their privacy policies, which can be found in the
Third-Party Privacy Policy
section below.
Third-Party SDKs
:
Integrated SDKs may collect the following:
Device information (e.g., model, OS version).
Advertising data (e.g., IDFA).
Fraud prevention data (e.g., click fraud).
Important
: We do not control the data collected by third-party SDKs.
5. Security
HaloPlus prioritizes the security of your information. While we take all reasonable precautions to protect your Non-Personal Information, no security system is entirely foolproof. We use encryption and secure storage methods to minimize risks.
6. Compliance with Regulations
For users in the
European Economic Area (EEA)
, the
United Kingdom
, and
Switzerland
, we process your data in compliance with the
EU General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR)
. You have the right to:
Request access to your collected data.
Request correction or deletion of your data.
Withdraw your consent at any time.
For users in California, we comply with the
California Consumer Privacy Act (CCPA)
, ensuring transparency and user control over collected data.
7. Changes to This Privacy Policy
We reserve the right to update or amend this Privacy Policy at any time. If you disagree with any changes, you may discontinue using the app. Continued use of the app after changes signifies your acceptance of the revised policy.
8. Contact Us
If you have questions, feedback, or concerns about this Privacy Policy or wish to report a violation, contact us at
admin@haloplus.vn
